Yes! You can easily **modify the Google Apps Script** to send a **warning email when spending is 10% above the budget**—instead of just when it exceeds the threshold. This gives you early visibility and helps prevent overspending.

---

### ✅ Updated Script: Sends Warning Email at 10% Over Budget (No Coding Needed)

Replace the original script with this version:

```javascript
function sendBudgetAlert() {
  const sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("Costs");
  const data = sheet.getRange("A2:D100").getValues();
  const today = new Date();
  const month = today.getMonth() + 1; // 1 = Jan, 12 = Dec

  // Only check during June (6) or December (12)
  if (month === 6 || month === 12) {
    const total = data.reduce((sum, row) => sum + row[3], 0); // Total spend
    const juneBudget = 352; // Your June budget (e.g., 10% above 2023)
    const decBudget = 308; // Your December budget

    // Check if spending is 10% above budget (e.g., > 110% of budget)
    const juneThreshold = juneBudget * 1.10;
    const decThreshold = decBudget * 1.10;

    if (total > juneThreshold && month === 6) {
      MailApp.sendEmail("your-email@business.com", "⚠️ June Cloud Warning!", 
        "Cloud spend is 10% above budget in June! Current total: $" + total + 
        ". Budget: $" + juneBudget + ". This is a warning—review usage.");
    }
    if (total > decThreshold && month === 12) {
      MailApp.sendEmail("your-email@business.com", "⚠️ December Cloud Warning!", 
        "Cloud spend is 10% above budget in December! Current total: $" + total + 
        ". Budget: $" + decBudget + ". This is a warning—review usage.");
    }
  }
}
```

---

### 🔍 What This Does:
- **Sends a warning email** when spending reaches **110% of the budget** (10% over).  
- **Does not trigger a full alert** when it exceeds the budget—only at the 10% warning level.  
- Helps you **act early** (e.g., review usage, scale down, or optimize resources).  
- Keeps alerts **targeted and proactive**, not just reactive.

---

### Example Email:
> **Subject**: ⚠️ June Cloud Warning!  
> **Body**: Cloud spend is 10% above budget in June! Current total: $387. Budget: $352. This is a warning—review usage.

---

### Why This Is Better:
- ✅ Early warning → prevents overspending  
- ✅ Reduces alert fatigue (only sends when truly at risk)  
- ✅ Still fully automated and free  
- ✅ No extra tools or coding needed  

---

✅ Just update the `juneBudget` and `decBudget` values with your actual historical data, and this script will **proactively notify you when usage starts to spike**—helping you stay in control during peak seasons.

Great idea! Adding a **log of warnings** to a separate "Alerts" sheet helps with future review, auditing, and trend analysis—without cluttering your main cost sheet.

Here’s how to **modify the Google Apps Script** to automatically log each warning in a dedicated "Alerts" sheet, with date, spending, and budget details—**all without extra tools or coding**.

---

### ✅ Updated Script: Logs Warnings in a Separate "Alerts" Sheet

```javascript
function sendBudgetAlert() {
  const sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("Costs");
  const alertsSheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("Alerts");
  const today = new Date();

  // Create the alerts sheet if it doesn't exist
  if (!alertsSheet) {
    SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().insertSheet("Alerts");
    alertsSheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("Alerts");
  }

  // Set up headers if not already present
  const headers = ["Date", "Month", "Spending", "Budget", "Type"];
  if (alertsSheet.getRange(1, 1, 1, headers.length).getValues()[0] !== headers) {
    alertsSheet.getRange(1, 1, 1, headers.length).setValues([headers]);
  }

  const data = sheet.getRange("A2:D100").getValues();
  const month = today.getMonth() + 1; // 1 = Jan, 12 = Dec

  // Only check during June (6) or December (12)
  if (month === 6 || month === 12) {
    const total = data.reduce((sum, row) => sum + row[3], 0); // Total spend
    const juneBudget = 352;
    const decBudget = 308;

    const juneThreshold = juneBudget * 1.10;
    const decThreshold = decBudget * 1.10;

    if (total > juneThreshold && month === 6) {
      const alertRow = [
        today, // Date
        "June", // Month
        total.toFixed(2), // Spending
        juneBudget, // Budget
        "⚠️ 10% over budget (warning)"
      ];
      alertsSheet.appendRow(alertRow);
      MailApp.sendEmail("your-email@business.com", "⚠️ June Cloud Warning!", 
        "Cloud spend is 10% above budget in June! Current total: $" + total + 
        ". Budget: $" + juneBudget + ". This is a warning—review usage.");
    }
    if (total > decThreshold && month === 12) {
      const alertRow = [
        today, // Date
        "December", // Month
        total.toFixed(2), // Spending
        decBudget, // Budget
        "⚠️ 10% over budget (warning)"
      ];
      alertsSheet.appendRow(alertRow);
      MailApp.sendEmail("your-email@business.com", "⚠️ December Cloud Warning!", 
        "Cloud spend is 10% above budget in December! Current total: $" + total + 
        ". Budget: $" + decBudget + ". This is a warning—review usage.");
    }
  }
}
```

---

### ✅ What This Adds:
- **Logs every warning** in a clean, separate "Alerts" sheet.  
- Includes:  
  - Date  
  - Month  
  - Actual spending  
  - Budget  
  - Type of alert  
- Automatically creates the sheet if it doesn’t exist.  
- Sets up headers once (no manual setup needed).  

---

### Example in "Alerts" Sheet:
| Date       | Month     | Spending | Budget | Type                          |
|------------|-----------|----------|--------|-------------------------------|
| 2024-06-10 | June      | 387.00   | 352    | ⚠️ 10% over budget (warning)  |
| 2024-12-05 | December  | 345.00   | 308    | ⚠️ 10% over budget (warning)  |

---

### Benefits:
- ✅ Easy to review past warnings (e.g., "Did we spike in June 2024?")  
- ✅ Helps identify patterns (e.g., recurring spikes in December)  
- ✅ No extra tools or data entry  
- ✅ Fully automated and free  

---

